> Does anybody know whether SyQuest's SyJet 1.5G Parallel Port Removable
> Hard Drive works with Linux, and if so, what options I would need to
> use with it?
I have had reports that it works with my (unsupported alpha) driver
for the EPST.  (See 
http://www.torque.net/parport/
)
> From the box, I note under "Technical Data" that it lists various
> flavours of Windows operating systems it will work under, then
> comments that it...
> 
>  Q> Will perform as EIDE compliant under UNIX or Novell Netware.
I believe there was an internal EIDE version of the drive.  AFAIK,
however, the external version was based on the original SCSI drive and
the Shuttle EPST adapter.
> It also notes on the box that a "SyQuest Provided Parallel Port to
> SCSI Adapter" is included, if that helps...
That's the EPST cable.
